UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304393295012184
KW  - Inflation
AB  - This paper presents a model of dynamically consistent monetary policy that explains changes in inflation over time. In the model — as in the postwar United States — adverse supply shocks trigger increases in inflation. High inflation persists until a tough policymaker causes a recession to disinflate. The paper also proposes an approach to selecting a unique equilibrium in infinite-horizon models of monetary policy.
